<br>
---<br>
<br>
oh how i wish there were no skald changes listed in those patch notes.  now i know that my favorite character will remain hopelessly gimped and worthless for at least the next 12, more likely 18 months.  so let us review the changes realistically shall we?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- Increased the range of the Chant of the Brawl line to 1500.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
this chant does not do enough damage to be useful in rvr.  period.  it is more productive for your skald to keep run song on so that people who drop from combat mode during the course of the battle have speed to get back into combat.  worse this change has no impact on pve, as your group 99% of the time is already within 700 of you.  this change is totally meaningless for the vast majority of skalds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- Decreased the reuse timer on the Warcry and Battle Shout lines to 15 seconds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
now we can DD for meaningless or zero damage more often.  however this does certainly improve our ability to solo for exp (if anyone can stomach that idea) and it also improves our dueling ability, especially vs minstrels.  this will help in making a duel with a minstrel who has any amount of ability to play his character not an auto-lose.  it has a VERY small possibility of helping in rvr, in that it is theoretically possible that you can interrupt casters during a battle more frequently.  the truth is however that a single interrupt on a single caster, when your opponents (such as reavers with pbae chant) can interrupt multiple casters, is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not likely</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to have a significant impact on the outcome of the battle.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- Added a new shout in the Warcry and Battle Shout lines. War Howl is a new level 43 shout and Battle Roar is a new level 50 shout.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
here we have one useful change.  now we have a 43 instead of a 34 DD.  that means fewer totally resisted shouts.  most skalds will have this, even those who spec 50 weapons so this is a notable change for them.  the 50 spec shout however is irrelevant.  no one who actually understands what a skald is supposed to do in rvr will choose this spec.  if skalds had 2.0 and shield this would be great though, it would allow a spec of 40ish weapon 50 songs 42 shield.  that is how a skald SHOULD look.  i would reactivate for six months immediately for that.  unfortunately it looks like it will never happen.<br>
<br>
the higher level DD (singular), when coupled with the lower recycle time, is a useful and appreciated change.  unfortunately this is not a SKALD change.  this was done to offset the change to minstrels.  anything skalds and minstrels both get is NOT a SKALD change.  in fact, the change to minstrels is actually a boon to them as it is useful already for them to spec to 50 for the highest AA chant.  on a side note, all damage chants were increased to 1500 range.  again, not a skald change.  so far the only skald change is to lower the DD timer to match that of an existing class we share little in common with.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- Skald base hit points have been raised.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
this, all around, is the worst choice.  it is illogical to begin with.  skalds already have essentially the same life totals as all other melee hybrids.  skalds dont die any more quickly than any other melee hybrid with the same armor and resists.  in fact, from recent personal experience in rvr i find that skalds live longer than most.  facing one of the more competent 8 man hib groups in emain this recent weekend i was the last in my group to die not once, but both times we fought them.  first 5 v 8, second 7 v 8.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>i did not live due to my personal resourcefulness.  i lived because the enemy did not deem it necessary to take the time to kill me until i was the last man standing.  i am known on sight to the majority of the enemies on my server and am known to be a competent player.  still my experienced enemies did not view me as a worthwhile threat to neutralize until all other threats were gone.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  the biggest problem with this specific change is that it is MOST likely to be viewed by decision makers at mythic as a long term &quot;fix&quot; to skalds.  when in reality it has either very little, or no impact on our rvr experience.  and it fails logic.  we are not light tanks.  why push our hits toward those of light tanks?  it makes no sense.<br>
<br>
here is the real problem in a nutshell.  mythic has not given up on the idea that where wardens are the magical chant class, and paladins are the defensive chant class, so skalds should be the offensive chant class.  the offensive class template is dead.  gone.  until mythic accepts that, skalds will continue to be the gimpy, far below average, sorry excuse for a melee hybrid that they are today.<br>
<br>
where are the real fixes?<br>
<br>
why do we have such highly resisted shouts?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PARTLY FIXED /CHEER</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
where is our 2.0 and shield spec?  there is no logical fix to the skald other than this that will make any worthwhile difference.  swap our small shields for evade 4 or 5 is an interesting idea, but without a self dex/quick buff that would be ineffective.  worse, it would not be in character.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not fixed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
where is a reason to spec anything but 50 sword/axe 43 songs, or 44/46/17?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not fixed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
why do we still have useless single resist chants?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not fixed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
why is there still no reason to group a skald other than run speed?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not fixed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
why is there nothing for a second skald in group to do that actually matters?  a thane, berserker, savage, warrior will fill that spot better.  meaning ANY other melee.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not fixed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
i am sad that on a day that could be so monumentous there is such a let down.  i WANT to play daoc.  i WANT to play my skald.  however after the last six months of playing a gimped character, which in the past had been a BALANCED character, i chose to not play either my skald or daoc any more.  past history has proven that changes in patch notes are never removed.  this one last time i am holding out hope that the past will not repeat itself.<br>
<br>
edit:<br>
<br>
long as i'm at it, how about those weapon changes eh?<br>
<br>
first off i know nothing about axe so i have no comment.<br>
<br>
demolish and frost hammer are both medium damage styles. adding demolish does nothing that a second frost hammer wouldn't do. nothing good that is. it does give your target stun immunity from worthwhile stuns like slam, and while you're at it you're more likely to wiff on demolish than on another frost hammer due to the lower chance to hit.<br>
<br>
the change to the level 50 style was good for warriors. and thanes i guess. but it's a hard call. warriors and thanes spec shield, and shield works much better and more often than parry which they normally dont spec. at least not high. the question here is: having it 3rd in a highly used chain still has the drawback of trying to land 3 styles in a row. but does that make it less useful than having it second in a style chain you're not going to use? for people like myself with my skald, i will never be able to spec to 50 hammer anyway so this is a moot point. add to that the 5 i can spec parry does not make the style particularly viable, neither does it's bleed effect which makes my target un-mezzable.<br>
<br>
WHERE IS MY TO HIT BONUS ON CONQUER?  <br>
<br>
taking away ice storm really screws over nearly all midgard melees who spec sword. making it evade reactionary helps shadowblades only off the top of my head. this should have been a change made only to shadowblade sword spec. this is a huge nerf for anyone who actually plays the game who is spec'd sword. assault does NO damage, so now if you need an anytime style you will sit and pound away with a 30% damage bonus.  or 35% for 5x the endurance with polar rift LOL.  i'm not counting those people of course who only have /stick /assist and back postional on their spellbar. but for them it is irrelevant anyway, so overall this does nothing for anyone but shadowblades and ONLY if it does more damage than hamstring.  i guess hunters can spec sword, but why they would over spear i cannot comprehend.  <br>
<br>
adding sifs to the new evade chain really is a wash.  sifs really wasn't used anyway, i can't recall ever landing rush when i was sword specd so i never had the opportunity to try it out.<br>
<br>
and then we have draw out.  ALL AGGRO STYLES SHOULD HAVE HAD TO HIT BONUSES FROM THE DAY THE GAME RELEASED.  the whole point of using an aggro style to start with is that when you need it, it is an EMERGENCY.  someone soft and squishy is dying.  if it wasn't, you wouldn't be needing it. is this a good change?  yes.<br>
<br>
ALL styles should have a to hit bonus.  the very short list of why i quit this game includes the dozens, if not hundreds, of times that my skald has wiffed with conquer on a mezd target.  styles that are not blocked by defense or bladeturn should hit EVERY TIME.<br>
<br>
skalds got screwed, and with styles not only skalds but all of midgard got screwed.  (and now for obligatory rant) when alb <br>
