<br>
As far as the increased range on the DD song goes, I'm surprised people are griping about it, since it was a requested change by many players.  It has been in many, many team lead reports over the past months. People asked for it, and we got it. <br>
<br>
My gut feeling is that they made the DD changes for the sake of Skalds, and then gave them to Minstrels because they have the same DD line we do.  I honestly don't see why it's a big deal. The changes make skalds more effective, people can disagree on how much.  I use my DDs several times in big fights, and now I'll get to use them 25% more, for more damage, with fewer resists.  I like that. <br>
<br>
I agree that more hit points was just a way of tossing us a bone. I'll take it, but I don't expect it to fix anything.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is that Mythic is going through its own process.  Giving us the same spec points as a Thane and the ability to spec shield is a huge change to the class.  Really, it makes us a different (much more powerful) class, and so they want to try other things first. <br>
<br>
