<br>
Worthless DD, too low level, too often resisted -&gt; partly adressed, 15 s timer is nice, so is the new level 43 bellow. But yes, the 50 shout is a gift to minstrels, not skalds. Right. But I think the timers and the level 43 shout will help a lot.<br>
<br>
The damage add range is more of a &quot;bad design decision&quot; fix, but it was a long standing issue. Even if the game has evolved so much as to make a 7dps dmg add mostly pointless, it is still a fix that makes sense.<br>
<br>
More hp is one way to adress skald survivability. Not defense. Survivability. It was requested, and needed. I am disappointed that they didn't put ways to DEFEND ourselves effectively (whether passively or actively) instead, but it is a shot at adressing an issue.<br>
<br>
With more damage, more hp, less resists (due to higher level bellow) they are trying to adress one of the bigges skald gripe, ie the &quot;mudflation vs. the static skald&quot; effect that has plagued our existence since release.<br>
<br>
So I don't think this patch is bad. It tries to adress the most prevalent issues we have outlined, in the various reports.<br>
<br>
But the big problem we all have, I think, with this patch, is that the most important skald problem (which has been time after time outlined in the skald reports), ie our lack of definition, lack of role, lack of identity has been forgotten. The number one issue.<br>
<br>
Mythic is doing an &quot;honest&quot; job at dressing the symptoms, and I will not blame them for doing so. But not the causes, the roots of the skald plight.<br>
<br>
My big concern is that the couple of hps added and the slightly better shout dps will only last as long as the next generic melee or hybrid &quot;love&quot; patch, or the next game systems overhaul - even if they will tremendously help now.<br>
<br>
I believe what we all expected was an attempt to cure the roots of the skald malaise by strongly defining or redefining the purpose and the point of playing a skald. More spec points and shield (ie : putting us as a fully defined melee hybrid), a new valuable combat song, abilities usable at range ... that would have been a less timid step, and probably a more perennial one.<br>
<br>
So wait and see how this patch will help ... <p>---------<br>
